{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Reject invalid HMAC signature with 401 and do not forward body to queue.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is between signature verification and queue handoff, not just pure hash logic. A unit test can prove compare logic, but can miss accidental enqueue on reject path. Rejected System because behavior text only requires HTTP status + no forward, which can be validated with in-process handler+queue wiring (no real OS/network dependency). Rejected Agentic/Workflow because no AI/ML step exists.","test_description":"Run handler with an in-memory request/response harness and a real queue interface implementation stub that records writes. Send body/header with mismatched HMAC; assert 401 and zero queue writes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Persist event to queue before returning HTTP 200 acknowledgment.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is an ordering/atomicity contract across modules (HTTP handler and persistent queue adapter). Unit is too low because ordering bug appears at handoff boundary. Rejected System because behavior text does not require real network/subprocess; local persistent backend (e.g., sqlite/file) in-process is sufficient. Rejected Agentic/Workflow due no model decisions.","test_description":"Use handler wired to real local persistent queue backend. Inject a controllable queue write delay/commit hook; verify 200 is not emitted until durable write succeeds, and failure before commit does not return 200.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.09,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Return HTTP response without waiting for downstream processing completion.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Behavior is decoupling between enqueue/ack path and async processor path, which is a module interaction issue. Unit-only tests can miss accidental await/join on processor future. Rejected System because real external infra is not required to detect blocking; an in-process slow processor suffices. Rejected Agentic/Workflow since no AI dependency.","test_description":"Wire handler + queue + downstream worker stub where worker blocks for a long time. Send valid event, assert response returns immediately after enqueue (before worker finishes).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.09,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Response arrives within 3 seconds wall-clock under slow concurrent downstream processing.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is a real runtime timing/concurrency requirement (wall-clock SLA under contention). In-process fakes/timers can hide event-loop starvation, socket backlog, and scheduler effects; real HTTP server/runtime behavior is the failure boundary. Rejected Integration because behavior text explicitly requires wall-clock timing under concurrency. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because no AI/ML step is involved.","test_description":"Start real Node HTTP server process, generate concurrent requests while earlier events trigger slow downstream work, and measure end-to-end latency over real sockets. Assert each ack <= 3s.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.23,"System":0.72,"Agentic":0.015,"Workflow":0.015}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Duplicate event ID is not written to queue twice.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Dedup correctness depends on state handoff between idempotency check/storage and queue write path. Unit tests of an ID set function miss race/ordering integration defects. Rejected System because no real OS/network requirement is stated; local persistent state + queue wiring catches real failure. Rejected Agentic/Workflow (no model output dependency).","test_description":"Run handler with persistent dedupe store and queue backend in-process. Submit same event ID twice; assert first is queued, second is rejected/ignored, and queue has one record for that ID.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"If queue reports full, handler returns 503 and Retry-After header.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Behavior verifies mapping of queue backpressure signal to HTTP semantics across module boundary. Unit on status mapping alone is too narrow because it may miss real propagation from queue adapter. Rejected System because behavior text says 'queue reports it is full' (signal handling), which can be reproduced in-process without real infra saturation. Rejected Agentic/Workflow due no AI steps.","test_description":"Wire handler to queue implementation/stub that returns a typed 'full' error. Send valid event; assert 503 and presence/value format of Retry-After.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"Persistent queue enforces configured capacity and rejects events exceeding limit.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This tests the real queue component with its persistence layer and capacity accounting, not a mock. Unit is too low because enforcement failures often occur at storage/state interaction boundaries. Rejected System because local DB/filesystem-backed queue fits Integration definition and no subprocess/real network is required by behavior text. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because no model dependency.","test_description":"Instantiate real persistent queue backend with small capacity (e.g., N)